This paper is about using meta-learning to improve deep learning performance in low-resource drug discovery projects. The paper focuses on assessing the efficiency of the Model-Agnostic Meta-Learning (MAML) algorithm and its variants in predicting chemical properties and activities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
